						               													<description>In Faux Raccords, players try to cooperate editing a movie without being able to communicate. Several modes of play are available, in which you will edit a Feature Film, Two Short Films, a Series, a Multi-Arcs Movie or found your own Production Company.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn, you will play a card from your hand in one of three different ways:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     placing a card face down in the Film&amp;#10;     placing a card face up in the Cut in order to use its power&amp;#10;     discarding a card in order to peek at a face down card in the Film.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then you draw a new card and add it to your hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends either when a player has no card to play on their turn, or when a player decides the movie is ready. The winning condition depends on the mode. For example, for the Feature Film, players need to obtain a row of 16 cards in ascending order.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
